examples.en: He never loses a single thing I say.
My watch loses three minutes every hour.
Without music, the film loses its integrity.
The painting loses something in this light.
If he loses the deal, he'll be badly out of pocket.
Ten demerits and he loses his privileges.
She never loses weight because she snacks between meals.
If the council loses the appeal, it will incur all the legal costs.
Brian never usually loses his temper - he must be having an off day.
The schizophrenic loses ability to abstract or do conceptual thinking.
It's a sad moment when a man loses his job and discovers that he is expendable.
